Scanad Kenya chief executive Betty Radier has been appointed managing director of the Kenya Tourism Board, the parastatal that markets Kenya as a tourist destination. She replaces Muriithi Ndegwa who left in February after serving two terms of six years.KTB director for marketing Jacinta Nzioka-Mbithi has been serving in an acting capacity. Radier has 18 years senior management experience in marketing, strategy and operations. She has worked with JWT and Scanad Advertising Tanzania, McCann Kenya, and Lowe Scanad Uganda. I have no doubt she is the right person to take the helm at the KTB as the corporation enters its 20th anniversary in 2017, KTB chairman Jimi Kariuki said.